    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yeah i get that it's complicated, but i've seen a lot of data suggesting that when benefits are too high, it basically just makes it more rational for people to stay home instead of taking low-wage jobs. like, if the gap between welfare and a paycheck is too small, why would anyone bother? don't you think that's a pretty direct driver of the declining participation rates we've seen?",
