    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get that there are other factors, but it feels like you're downplaying the incentive issue a lot. if we just kept the safety net smaller and more targeted, wouldn't we see a much stronger push for people to enter the workforce? isn't it fair to say that the current level of support is actively undermining the labor market's efficiency?",
